          "node": {
            "created_at": "1776693969",
            "text": "Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang unveiled NemoClaw at GTC 2026, marking a strategic move to transform the viral OpenClaw project into a secure, enterprise-ready platform. Described by Huang as the \"operating system for personal AI,\" the stack allows businesses to deploy autonomous agents that can navigate complex workflows using a single terminal command. Unlike basic chatbots, these \"claws\" use a new runtime called OpenShell to operate within isolated sandboxes, ensuring that sensitive corporate data stays protected while the agents perform multi-step tasks like troubleshooting API failures or managing customer billing.\n\nThe launch is supported by a broad coalition of partners, including Salesforce, Adobe, and SAP, who are integrating NemoClaw into their own business ecosystems. By pairing these agents with Nvidia’s new DGX Spark \"desktop supercomputers,\" companies can run high-reasoning tasks locally to avoid the latency and high costs of cloud-based inference. This infrastructure shift signals Nvidia's intent to become the foundational layer for a \"digital workforce\" where autonomous agents don't just answer questions, but actively execute the administrative and technical labor of a global enterprise.\n\nWill your next coworker be an autonomous claw running on your desk?\n\nFollow @ai.rise.co\n\n#fyp #life #ai",
            "id": "18181321069376935"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
